Original Authorship of Novel Algorithms and Architecture
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

The following algorithms, control loops, metrics, and architectural designs
contained in this repository were originally conceived, designed, and
authored by Sandip Patel:

  1. ATQB — Autonomous Token-Quota Balancing
     A PID-inspired control-loop algorithm for governing LLM token quotas
     and Hard-Limit Budgets (HLB) across heterogeneous workloads, including
     the decision ladder (allow / quota_shift / throttle / downgrade /
     hard_stop) and the Marginal Utility of Accuracy (MUA) model-tier
     downgrade evidence using Beta-posterior success probabilities.
     Implemented in: src/agentic_finops/atqb/

  2. UCI — Unit Cost of Inference
     A composite per-task fiscal metric combining weighted token cost,
     compute overhead, and SLO-latency penalty, normalized over successful
     tasks. Implemented in: src/agentic_finops/uci/

  3. MAG — Multi-Agent Governance Orchestration
     The agent topology (Sentinel, Balancer, Broker, Optimizer, Guardrail)
     and the inter-agent message contracts for closed-loop FinOps decisions
     across multi-cloud LLM inference workloads.
     Implemented in: src/agentic_finops/mag/

  4. Agentic FinOps Reference Architecture
     The end-to-end architecture connecting cost-signal adapters, the ATQB
     control loop, the MAG agent mesh, the UCI metric pipeline, the policy
     guardrails, and the live dashboard.

These contributions are described in the author's research paper
"Agentic FinOps: Autonomous Token-Quota Balancing and Unit-Cost Inference
Governance for Multi-Agent LLM Workloads" (Sandip Patel, 2026).

